properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 12 at 3:28AM CST until February 13 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Accumulating snow this afternoon and tonight...

.Snow, possibly mixed with rain to start, will overspread parts
of far northeast Missouri, far southeast Iowa and Illinois this
afternoon and tonight. Total snow accumulations of 2 to 4 inches
are expected. Significantly colder air will move into the area
Thursday with some blowing snow possible.

* WHAT...Very cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low as
20 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of east central, northeast and southeast Iowa.

* WHEN...From midnight tonight to noon CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on
exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM MIDNIGHT TONIGHT TO NOON CST THURSDAY
